VentureBeat has published leaked official renders of the Samsung Galaxy S9 and Galaxy S9+. The new smartphones retain the bezel-less display of the previous generation and feature improved cameras. According to the report, the Galaxy S9 will have a 5.8-inch display with 4GB of RAM and 64GB storage capacity, while the Galaxy S9+ will sport a 6.2-inch panel, 6GB of RAM, and 128GB of storage. No rear renders of the smartphones were published, but the report stated that the fingerprint sensor will be located benearth the camera on both devices. Samsung is set to officially unveil the Galaxy S9 and Galaxy S9+ smartphones at Mobile Word Congress on 25 February 2018.